ciscoGsccpMIB.description: The MIB for signalling Connection Control Part(SCCP) messages transported over Signalling System No. 7 (SS7) Network via Cisco IP Transfer Point. This MIB provides information specified in ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network. The Cisco IP Transfer Point (ITP) is a hardware and software solution that transports SS7 traffic using IP. Each ITP node provides function similar to SS7 Signalling point. The relevant ITU documents describing this technology is the ITU Q series, including ITU Q.700: Introduction to CCITT Signalling System No. 7 and ITU Q.701 Functional description of the message transfer part (MTP) of Signalling System No. 7. The IETF Working Group Signalling Transport (SIGTRAN) has defined MTP3 User Adaptation (M3UA) and SCCP User Adaptation (SUA) protocols. The drafts can be found at: http://www.ietf.org/html.charters/sigtran-charter.html This MIB consists of the following tables: Instance Table Concerned Point Code List Table Mated Application (MAP) Table Global Title Translation (GTT) Selector Table Global Title Address (GTA) Table Application Group Table Prefix Conversion Table Translation Entries Table Global Title Errors Table Abbreviations: CDPA - Called Party Address CGPA - Calling Party Address CLLI - Common Language Location Codes CR - Connection Request message CREF - Connection Refusal message DPC - Destination Point Code ERR - Error message GTA - Global Title Address GTI - Global Title Indicator GTT - Global Title Translation LUDT - long unitdata message LUDTS - long unitdata service message M2PA - MTP2 Peer-to-Peer Adaptation Layer M3UA - MTP3-User Adaptation MAP - Mated Application Table MSU - Message Signal Unit MTP - Message Transport Protocol MTP2 - Layer 2 of Message Transport Protocol MTP3 - Layer 3 of Message Transport Protocol NAI - Nature of Address Indicator NP - Numbering Plan OPC - Originating Point Code PC - Point Code RTN - Route Table Name RSR - Reset Request message SCCP - Signalling Connection Control Part SCTP - Stream Transmission Protocol(RFC 2960) SI - Signalling Indicator SP - Signalling Point SLC - Signalling Link Code SLS - Signalling Link Selector SSN - Subsystem Number SUA - SCCP-User Adaptation TFR - Transfer Restricted messages TT - Title Translation UDT - unitdata message UDTS - unitdata service message XUDT - extended unitdata message XUDTS - extended unitdata service message

CgsccpConPcListName.name: CgsccpConPcListName
CgsccpConPcListName.description: The configured name associated with SCCP GTT Concerned Point Code list name.

CgsccpGttSelName.name: CgsccpGttSelName
CgsccpGttSelName.description: The configured name associated with SCCP GTT Selector.

CgsccpGttAppName.name: CgsccpGttAppName
CgsccpGttAppName.description: The configured name associated with SCCP GTT Application Group.

CgsccpGttPrefName.name: CgsccpGttPrefName
CgsccpGttPrefName.description: The configured name associated with SCCP GTT Prefix Conversion table. This name is supported as octet string containing administrative information in human-readable form. The use of control codes should be avoided. The use of newline should be avoided. The use of leading or trailing white space should be avoided.

CgsccpGttDisplaySS.name: CgsccpGttDisplaySS
CgsccpGttDisplaySS.description: The subsystem number in display format.

CgsccpGttAppCost.name: CgsccpGttAppCost
CgsccpGttAppCost.description: The cost associated with an entry in SCCP GTT Application Group.

CgsccpGttAppType.name: CgsccpGttAppType
CgsccpGttAppType.description: The list of application types in Application Group 'pc' : The application type is a point code. 'pcssn' : The application type is a point code and subsystem number (SSN). 'as' : The application type is an M3UA or SUA Application Server (AS).

CgsccpGttMapType.name: CgsccpGttMapType
CgsccpGttMapType.description: The list of SCCP GTT Mated Application type 'primary' : The mated application is primary 'backup' : The mated application is backup.

CgsccpGttGtaResType.name: CgsccpGttGtaResType
CgsccpGttGtaResType.description: The list of SCCP GTT Result Type 'pc' : The GTA translates to a point code. 'pcssn' : The GTA translates to a point code and optional SSN 'app' : The GTA translates to a GTT Application Group. 'as' : The GTA translates to an M3UA or SUA Application Server (AS) name.

CgsccpGttRoutingInd.name: CgsccpGttRoutingInd
CgsccpGttRoutingInd.description: The SCCP GTT Routing Indicator 'ri2gt' : Set RI to GT 'ri2ssn' : Set RI to SSN 'ssnRI2ssn' : Replace SSN and set RI to GT 'ssnRI2gt' : Replace SSN and set RI to SSN 'replTT' : Replace the TT 'riNotAppl' : RI is not applicable 'riUndef' : RI is undefined.

CgsccpGttMapPcStatus.name: CgsccpGttMapPcStatus
CgsccpGttMapPcStatus.description: The list of SCCP GTT Mated App point code status 'allowed' : The mated application is allowed 'prohibited' : The mated application is prohibited.

CgsccpGttMapSsStatus.name: CgsccpGttMapSsStatus
CgsccpGttMapSsStatus.description: The list of SCCP GTT Mated App subsystem status 'allowed' : The mated application is allowed 'prohibited' : The mated application is prohibited.

CgsccpGttMultInd.name: CgsccpGttMultInd
CgsccpGttMultInd.description: The list of SCCP GTT Multiplicity Indicator 'solitary' : The application is solitary 'shared' : The application is shared 'dominant' : The application is dominant 'cost' : The application uses cost 'cgpa' : The application is shared and uses calling party address and weighting factor. 'wrr' : The application is shared and uses weighting factor

CgsccpGttMapCongStatus.name: CgsccpGttMapCongStatus
CgsccpGttMapCongStatus.description: The list of SCCP GTT Mated App congestion status 'NotCong' : The point code not congested 'CongLevel1' : The congestion level 1 'CongLevel2' : The congestion level 2 'CongLevel3' : The congestion level 3.

CgsccpGttQOS.name: CgsccpGttQOS
CgsccpGttQOS.description: The SCCP GTT Quality of Service (QOS). The '255' value indicates that QOS is not configured.

CgsccpGttGlobalTitleInd.name: CgsccpGttGlobalTitleInd
CgsccpGttGlobalTitleInd.description: The SCCP GTT Global Title Indicator (GTI). The following values are generally used: No global title included (0), For ITU, GT includes NAI only (1), For ANSI, GT includes TT, NP and encoding scheme (1), GT includes only TT (2), GT includes TT, NP and encoding scheme (3), GT includes TT, NP, encoding scheme, NAI (4), Maximum GTI (15), Invalid GTI (253), Wild GTI (254).
CgsccpGttGlobalTitleInd.reference: The Global Title Indicator is defined in the International Telecommunication Union standard Q.713: Specifications of Signalling System No. 7 - Signalling Connection Control Part (SCCP) section 3.4.1 Address Indicator.

CgsccpClass.name: CgsccpClass
CgsccpClass.description: The SCCP class of service involved 'class0' : class 0 of SCCP 'class1' : class 1 of SCCP 'class2' : class 2 of SCCP 'class3' : class 3 of SCCP 'class4' : class 4 of SCCP

cgsccpGttTranslateSample.name: cgsccpGttTranslateSample
cgsccpGttTranslateSample.description: The length of the sample interval used to collect number of maximum Global Title Translations per second.

cgsccpGttTranslatePeriod.name: cgsccpGttTranslatePeriod
cgsccpGttTranslatePeriod.description: The length of the period used to collect the maximum Global Title Translations rate. Samples are calculated for the time period specified by the cgsccpGttTranslateSample object.

cgsccpGttMapStateNotifEnabled.name: cgsccpGttMapStateNotifEnabled
cgsccpGttMapStateNotifEnabled.description: The Map state notification truth value. 'true' Indicates that the ciscoGsccpGttMapStateChange notification is to be generated when the state changes. That is, the notification generation is enabled. 'false' Indicates that the ciscoGsccpGttMapStateChange notification generation is disabled.

cgsccpGttLoadTableNotifEnabled.name: cgsccpGttLoadTableNotifEnabled
cgsccpGttLoadTableNotifEnabled.description: The GTT load table notification truth value. 'true' Indicates that the ciscoGsccpGttLoadTable notification is to be generated when the a configuration is loaded. That is, the notification generation is enabled. 'false' Indicates that the ciscoGsccpGttLoadTable notification generation is disabled.

cgsccpGttTransErrorsNotifEnabled.name: cgsccpGttTransErrorsNotifEnabled
cgsccpGttTransErrorsNotifEnabled.description: The global title translation errors notification truth value as follows. 'true' Indicates that the ciscoGsccpGttErrors notification is to be generated when the a configuration is loaded. That is, the notification generation is enabled. 'false' Indicates that the ciscoGsccpGttErrors notification generation is disabled.

cgsccpGttErrorPeriod.name: cgsccpGttErrorPeriod
cgsccpGttErrorPeriod.description: The length of the sample window used to collect global title translations errors.

cgsccpGttErrorRecoveryCount.name: cgsccpGttErrorRecoveryCount
cgsccpGttErrorRecoveryCount.description: The number contiguous sample windows that have to be error free before the ciscoGsccpGttErrors notifications will be generated indicating end of global title translation errors condition.

cgsccpInstTable.name: cgsccpInstTable
cgsccpInstTable.description: SCCP information per instance of signalling point.

cgsccpInstTableEntry.name: cgsccpInstTableEntry
cgsccpInstTableEntry.description: Global Title information per instance of signalling point.

cgsccpInstXUDTSMsgsSent.description: This counter is incremented every time an extended unitdata service (XUDTS) message is sent (Q752/9 bis.14).

cgsccpInstQ752T7E1.name: cgsccpInstQ752T7E1

cgsccpInstQ752T7E1.description: This counter is incremented every time a translation was requested for a combination of Translation Type, Numbering Plan and Nature of Address for which no translation exists in the signalling point. This occurs when no selector is available for the combination of parameters provided in the MSU.

cgsccpInstInvalidGttFormat.name: cgsccpInstInvalidGttFormat
cgsccpInstInvalidGttFormat.reference: Q752 - Monitoring and measurements for SS7 Network table 7 entry 8. ANSI GR-82-CORE 6.4.2 System Total Measurements Item 9.
cgsccpInstInvalidGttFormat.description: This counter is incremented every time an invalid Global Title format is found while performing the global title translation. This counter provides information related to the Q752 table 7 entry 8 measurement indicating syntax error detected in MSU

cgsccpInstQ752T7E13.name: cgsccpInstQ752T7E13
cgsccpInstQ752T7E13.reference: Q752 - Monitoring and measurements for SS7 Network table 7 entry 13
cgsccpInstQ752T7E13.description: This counter is incremented every time a hop count violation is found in the MSU.

cgsccpInstMapNotFound.name: cgsccpInstMapNotFound
cgsccpInstMapNotFound.description: This counter is incremented every time a global title translation is successful to a certain PC/SSN but it was not found in the GTT Mated Application table.

cgsccpInstQ752T7E7.name: cgsccpInstQ752T7E7
cgsccpInstQ752T7E7.reference: Q752 - Monitoring and measurements for SS7 Network table 7 entry 13
cgsccpInstQ752T7E7.description: This counter is incremented every time a global title translation could not be performed due to an unequipped subsystem (SS).

cgsccpInstGttConfigStatus.name: cgsccpInstGttConfigStatus
cgsccpInstGttConfigStatus.description: The status of the current load or status from the prior load operation.

cgsccpInstConfigTS.name: cgsccpInstConfigTS
cgsccpInstConfigTS.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the last creation or deletion or modification of an entry in the cgsccpGttConPcTable, cgsccpGttMapTable, cgsccpGttSelTable, cgsccpGttGtaTable, cgsccpGttAppGr2Table, or cgsccpGttPref2Table. If the local network management subsystem is re-initialization, then this object contains the sysUpTime at the time when this occurred. This value can be used to prevent unnecessary walks of the these tables.

cgsccpInstGttConfigTS.name: cgsccpInstGttConfigTS
cgsccpInstGttConfigTS.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the last load of the GTT table using file format.

cgsccpInstLastURL.name: cgsccpInstLastURL
cgsccpInstLastURL.description: The URL used to load GTT tables.

cgsccpInstConPcTableEntries.name: cgsccpInstConPcTableEntries

cgsccpInstMapTableEntries.name: cgsccpInstMapTableEntries
cgsccpInstMapTableEntries.description: The number of entries in the cgsccpGttMapTable Table for this instance. Or in other words, the number of GTT Mated Application entries for this signalling point.

cgsccpInstGtaTableEntries.name: cgsccpInstGtaTableEntries
cgsccpInstGtaTableEntries.description: The number of entries in the cgsccpGttGtaTable Table for this instance. Or in other words, the number of GTT Global Title Address Table entries for this signalling point.

cgsccpInstSelTableEntries.name: cgsccpInstSelTableEntries
cgsccpInstSelTableEntries.description: The number of entries in the cgsccpGttSelTable Table for this instance. Or in other words, the number of GTT Selector Table entries for this signalling point.

cgsccpInstAppGrTableEntries.name: cgsccpInstAppGrTableEntries
cgsccpInstAppGrTableEntries.description: The number of entries in the cgsccpGttAppGrTable Table for this instance. Or in other words, the number of GTT Application Group Table entries for this signalling point.

cgsccpInstRowStatus.name: cgsccpInstRowStatus
cgsccpInstRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cgsccpInstTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

cgsccpInstPrefTableEntries.name: cgsccpInstPrefTableEntries
cgsccpInstPrefTableEntries.description: The number of entries in the cgsccpGttPref2Table Table for this instance. Or in other words, the number of GTT prefix conversion table entries for this signalling point.

cgsccpInstQ752Unqualified.name: cgsccpInstQ752Unqualified
cgsccpInstQ752Unqualified.description: This counter is incremented every time a global title translation is unsuccessful and the error type not covered by other specific error types.

cgsccpInstErrorIndicator.description: This object indicates whether global title translation errors have occurred in last interval specified by the cgsccpGttErrorPeriod object.

cgsccpInstReassUnsup.description: This counter is incremented every time a SCCP message is dropped due to an unsupported reassembly feature at this instance.

cgsccpInstReassFail.name: cgsccpInstReassFail
cgsccpInstReassFail.description: This counter is incremented every time a SCCP message is dropped due to a reassembly failure at this instance.

cgsccpInstSegUnsup.name: cgsccpInstSegUnsup

cgsccpInstSegFail.name: cgsccpInstSegFail

cgsccpGttConPcTable.name: cgsccpGttConPcTable
cgsccpGttConPcTable.description: A table of concerned point codes.

cgsccpGttAppGrEntNum.name: cgsccpGttAppGrEntNum

cgsccpGttAppGrRefCount.name: cgsccpGttAppGrRefCount

cgsccpGttAppGrAsName.name: cgsccpGttAppGrAsName

cgsccpGttMapPcStatus.description: The GTT MAP point code status.

cgsccpGttMapMultInd.name: cgsccpGttMapMultInd
cgsccpGttMapMultInd.description: The GTT mated application multiplicity indicator.

cgsccpGttMapBackupPc.name: cgsccpGttMapBackupPc
cgsccpGttMapBackupPc.description: The backup point code for the mated Application. The special value of zero indicates that no backup point code has been specified.

cgsccpGttMapBackupSsn.description: The backup subsystem number for the mated Application. The special value of zero indicates that no backup subsystem number has been specified.

cgsccpGttMapConPcList.description: The concerned point code list for the mated Application. The null string indicates that no concerned point code list has been specified.

cgsccpGttMapLastSsUsed.name: cgsccpGttMapLastSsUsed

cgsccpGttMapQ752T7E4.description: This counter is incremented every time a point code is congested at the GTT Mated Application.

cgsccpGttMapQ752T7E5.name: cgsccpGttMapQ752T7E5
cgsccpGttMapQ752T7E5.reference: Q752 - Monitoring and measurements for SS7 Network table 7 entry 5
cgsccpGttMapQ752T7E5.description: This counter is incremented every time a subsystem is unavailable at the GTT Mated Application.

cgsccpGttMapQ752T7E6.name: cgsccpGttMapQ752T7E6
cgsccpGttMapQ752T7E6.reference: Q752 - Monitoring and measurements for SS7 Network table 7 entry 6
cgsccpGttMapQ752T7E6.description: This counter is incremented every time a subsystem is congested at the GTT Mated Application.

cgsccpGttMapRefCount.name: cgsccpGttMapRefCount

cgsccpGttMapCongStatus.name: cgsccpGttMapCongStatus

cgsccpGttQ752T7E2.name: cgsccpGttQ752T7E2

cgsccpGttGtaTable.description: A table of SCCP Global Title Address entries.

cgsccpGttGtaTableEntry.name: cgsccpGttGtaTableEntry
cgsccpGttGtaTableEntry.description: A list of SCCP Global Title Address attributes.

cgsccpGttGtaAddr.name: cgsccpGttGtaAddr
cgsccpGttGtaAddr.description: The Global Title Address is 8 octets of the Called Party Address (CDPA).

cgsccpGttGtaSelName.name: cgsccpGttGtaSelName

cgsccpGttGtaRoutingInd.name: cgsccpGttGtaRoutingInd
cgsccpGttGtaRoutingInd.description: The SCCP GTT GTA specifies the routing indicator. When cgsccpGttGtaResType is 'pc' or 'pcssn', this object has a valid routing indicator. When cgsccpGttGtaResType is 'app' or 'as', the routing indicator is not applicable.

cgsccpGttGtaQOS.name: cgsccpGttGtaQOS
cgsccpGttGtaQOS.description: The SCCP GTT GTA specifies the QOS.

cgsccpGttGtaAddrDisp.name: cgsccpGttGtaAddrDisp
cgsccpGttGtaAddrDisp.description: The ASCII display string of Global Title Address up to 64 hex digits of the Called Party Address (CDPA). A zero length string specifies a default GTA value for the selector.

cgsccpGttGtaAddrLen.name: cgsccpGttGtaAddrLen
cgsccpGttGtaAddrLen.description: The number of hex digits in the Global Title Address of the Called Party Address (CDPA). For a default GTA, the address length is zero.

cgsccpGttPrefTable.name: cgsccpGttPrefTable
cgsccpGttPrefTable.description: A table of SCCP GTT Prefix Conversion Table entries. When a packet with GTA is received, it may need global title translation depending on Translation Type (TT), Numbering Plan (NP), Network Address Indicator (NAI) and Global Title Indicator (GTI) present in the packet. To perform the translation a selector (cgsccpGttSelTable) corresponding to TT, NP, NAI and GTI is used. The selector also specifies prefix conversion of the GTA before (pre) performing the global title translation or after (post) performing the global title translation. A selector can specify any or both (pre and post) prefix conversion tables. The prefix conversion involves matching of GTA digits in the cgsccpGttPrefInAddr and then replacing those digits with the digits in cgsccpGttPrefOutAddr.

cgsccpGttPrefTableEntry.name: cgsccpGttPrefTableEntry
cgsccpGttPrefTableEntry.description: A list of SCCP GTT Prefix Conversion attributes.

cgsccpGttPrefName.name: cgsccpGttPrefName
cgsccpGttPrefName.description: The GTT Prefix Conversion table name.

cgsccpGttPrefInAddr.name: cgsccpGttPrefInAddr
cgsccpGttPrefInAddr.description: If the GTA of the Called Party Address (CDPA) matches the digits in this object, then the prefix conversion is performed.

cgsccpGttPrefOutAddr.name: cgsccpGttPrefOutAddr
cgsccpGttPrefOutAddr.description: If the GTA of the Called Party Address (CDPA) matches the digits in cgsccpGttPrefInAddr then this object is used in the prefix conversion.

cgsccpGttPrefTblNAI.name: cgsccpGttPrefTblNAI
cgsccpGttPrefTblNAI.description: Nature of Address Indicator (NAI) for the Prefix Conversion Table.

cgsccpGttPrefTblNP.name: cgsccpGttPrefTblNP
cgsccpGttPrefTblNP.description: Numbering Plan (NP) for the Prefix Conversion Table.

cgsccpGttPrefItemNAI.name: cgsccpGttPrefItemNAI
cgsccpGttPrefItemNAI.description: Nature of Address Indicator (NAI) for the current item in this Prefix Conversion Table.

cgsccpGttPrefItemNP.name: cgsccpGttPrefItemNP
cgsccpGttPrefItemNP.description: Numbering Plan (NP) for the current item in this Prefix Conversion Table.

cgsccpGttPrefRowStatus.name: cgsccpGttPrefRowStatus
cgsccpGttPrefRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cgsccpGttPrefTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

cgsccpGttTranslateTable.name: cgsccpGttTranslateTable
cgsccpGttTranslateTable.description: The translate table contains a history of the number of global title packets that were translated on the various processors enabled for this function. The ability to translate GTT is critical to many SS7 functions. This table provides peak utilization to allow planning of maximum load on SS7 network.

cgsccpGttTranslateTableEntry.name: cgsccpGttTranslateTableEntry
cgsccpGttTranslateTableEntry.description: A list of global title translate statistics.

cgsccpGttTranslateSlot.name: cgsccpGttTranslateSlot
cgsccpGttTranslateSlot.description: The slot number containing the CPU that is performing Global Title translation.

cgsccpGttTranslateEntry.name: cgsccpGttTranslateEntry
cgsccpGttTranslateEntry.description: The entry number. Each entry represents a period of time as specified by the cgsccpGttTranslatePeriod object. The entries are ordered from old to new.

cgsccpGttTranslateRate.name: cgsccpGttTranslateRate
cgsccpGttTranslateRate.description: During each interval the rate of global title translations is calculated every second. This object is the highest rate of global title translation encountered in the interval specified by the cgsccpGttTranslatePeriod object.

cgsccpGttTranslateTS.name: cgsccpGttTranslateTS
cgsccpGttTranslateTS.description: This timestamp indicates when time period ended for this sample.

cgsccpGttTranslatePhysicalIndex.name: cgsccpGttTranslatePhysicalIndex
cgsccpGttTranslatePhysicalIndex.description: The entPhysicalIndex of the physical entity for which the statistics in this entry are maintained. The physical entity can be a CPU chip, a group of CPUs, a CPU card etc. The exact type of this entity is described by its entPhysicalVendorType value. If the CPU statistics in this entry correspond to more than one physical entity (or to no physical entity), or if the entPhysicalTable is not supported on the SNMP agent, the value of this object must be zero.

cgsccpGttPref2Table.name: cgsccpGttPref2Table
cgsccpGttPref2Table.description: A table of SCCP GTT Prefix Conversion Table entries. This table replaces the cgsccpGttPrefTable tables and allow prefix conversion to be specified per instance. When a packet with GTA is received, it may need global title translation depending on Translation Type (TT), Numbering Plan (NP), Network Address Indicator (NAI) and Global Title Indicator (GTI) present in the packet. To perform the translation a selector (cgsccpGttSelTable) corresponding to TT, NP, NAI and GTI is used. The selector also specifies prefix conversion of the GTA before (pre) performing the global title translation or after (post) performing the global title translation. A selector can specify any or both (pre and post) prefix conversion tables. The prefix conversion involves matching of GTA digits in the cgsccpGttPref2InAddr and then replacing those digits with the digits in cgsccpGttPref2OutAddr.

cgsccpGttPref2TableEntry.name: cgsccpGttPref2TableEntry
cgsccpGttPref2TableEntry.description: A list of SCCP GTT Prefix Conversion attributes.

cgsccpGttPref2Name.name: cgsccpGttPref2Name
cgsccpGttPref2Name.description: The GTT Prefix Conversion table name.

cgsccpGttPref2InAddr.name: cgsccpGttPref2InAddr
cgsccpGttPref2InAddr.description: If the GTA of the Called Party Address (CDPA) matches the digits in this object, then the prefix conversion is performed.

cgsccpGttPref2OutAddr.name: cgsccpGttPref2OutAddr
cgsccpGttPref2OutAddr.description: If the GTA of the Called Party Address (CDPA) matches the digits in cgsccpGttPref2InAddr then this object is used in the prefix conversion.

cgsccpGttPref2TblNAI.name: cgsccpGttPref2TblNAI
cgsccpGttPref2TblNAI.description: Nature of Address Indicator (NAI) for the Prefix Conversion Table.

cgsccpGttPref2TblNP.name: cgsccpGttPref2TblNP
cgsccpGttPref2TblNP.description: Numbering Plan (NP) for the Prefix Conversion Table.

cgsccpGttPref2ItemNAI.name: cgsccpGttPref2ItemNAI
cgsccpGttPref2ItemNAI.description: Nature of Address Indicator (NAI) for the current item in this Prefix Conversion Table.

cgsccpGttPref2ItemNP.name: cgsccpGttPref2ItemNP
cgsccpGttPref2ItemNP.description: Numbering Plan (NP) for the current item in this Prefix Conversion Table.

cgsccpGttPref2EncodingScheme.description: The encoding scheme to be used for output GTT address as follows. unknown - encoding scheme is not specified at the address level. bcdOdd - Use BCD odd encoding scheme. bcdEven - Use BCD even encoding scheme. national - national specific.

cgsccpGttAppGr2Table.name: cgsccpGttAppGr2Table
cgsccpGttAppGr2Table.description: A table of SCCP GTT Application Group Table entries.

cgsccpGttAppGr2TableEntry.name: cgsccpGttAppGr2TableEntry
cgsccpGttAppGr2TableEntry.description: A list of SCCP GTT Application Group attributes.

cgsccpGttAppGr2Pc.name: cgsccpGttAppGr2Pc
cgsccpGttAppGr2Pc.description: The point code specified by the item in the GTT Application Group. When the cgsccpGttAppGr2Type object has 'pc' or pcssn' values this object is required when entry is created. Otherwise, this value does not apply and can default to zero.

cgsccpGttAppGr2Ssn.name: cgsccpGttAppGr2Ssn
cgsccpGttAppGr2Ssn.description: The subsystem number (SSN) specified by the item in the GTT Application Group. It is valid only when cgsccpGttAppGr2Type is 'pcssn'. Otherwise it is zero.

cgsccpGttAppGr2Ri.name: cgsccpGttAppGr2Ri
cgsccpGttAppGr2Ri.description: The routing indicator (RI) specified by the item in the GTT Application Group.

cgsccpGttAppGr2RefCount.name: cgsccpGttAppGr2RefCount
cgsccpGttAppGr2RefCount.description: The number of global title addresses referring to this application group.

cgsccpGttAppGr2AsName.name: cgsccpGttAppGr2AsName
cgsccpGttAppGr2AsName.description: The Application Server (AS) name specified by the item in the GTT Application Group. It is valid only when cgsccpGttAppGr2Type is 'as'. Otherwise it is a zero length string.

cgsccpGttAppGr2NewSsn.name: cgsccpGttAppGr2NewSsn
cgsccpGttAppGr2NewSsn.description: The new subsystem number (SSN) specified by the item in the GTT Application Group. It is valid only when cgsccpGttAppGr2Type is 'as'. Otherwise it is zero.

cgsccpGttAppGr2NumUsed.name: cgsccpGttAppGr2NumUsed
cgsccpGttAppGr2NumUsed.description: The number of times this item in the GTT Application Group is used successfully.

cgsccpGttAppGr2Network.name: cgsccpGttAppGr2Network
cgsccpGttAppGr2Network.description: The processing of global title translation may result in a packet being transferred from one network to another. This object specifies the target network.

cgsccpGttAppGr2RowStatus.name: cgsccpGttAppGr2RowStatus
cgsccpGttAppGr2RowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cgsccpGttAppGr2Table following the RowStatus textual convention.

cgsccpGttErrorsTable.name: cgsccpGttErrorsTable
cgsccpGttErrorsTable.description: This table is used to indicate errors in global title translation and will be used to provide information for ciscoGsccpGttErrors notification.

cgsccpGttErrorsTableEntry.name: cgsccpGttErrorsTableEntry
cgsccpGttErrorsTableEntry.description: All objects in this table are derived from other objects in this MIB. At the end of each interval the values of these objects will be updated with number of errors that occurred during last interval. The length of the interval is defined by the cgsccpGttErrorPeriod object.

cgsccpGttErrorsSelectorNotFound.name: cgsccpGttErrorsSelectorNotFound
cgsccpGttErrorsSelectorNotFound.description: This counter is incremented every time a translation was requested for a combination of Translation Type, Numbering Plan and Nature of Address for which no translation exists in the signalling point. This occurs when no selector is available for the combination of parameters provided in the MSU. This counter is derived from cgsccpInstQ752T7E1 object.

cgsccpGttErrorsIncorrectFormat.name: cgsccpGttErrorsIncorrectFormat
cgsccpGttErrorsIncorrectFormat.description: This counter is incremented every time an invalid Global Title format is found while performing the global title translation. This counter is derived from cgsccpInstInvalidGttFormat object.

cgsccpGttErrorsGtaNotFound.name: cgsccpGttErrorsGtaNotFound
cgsccpGttErrorsGtaNotFound.description: This counter is incremented every time a global title title translations was required and a selector was not found. This counter is derived from cgsccpGttQ752T7E2 object.

cgsccpGttErrorsHopViolation.name: cgsccpGttErrorsHopViolation
cgsccpGttErrorsHopViolation.description: This counter is incremented every time a hop count violation is found in the MSU. This counter is derived from cgsccpInstQ752T7E13 object.

cgsccpGttErrorsMapNotFound.name: cgsccpGttErrorsMapNotFound
cgsccpGttErrorsMapNotFound.description: This counter is incremented every time a global title translation is successful to a certain PC/SSN but it was not found in the GTT Mated Application table. This counter is derived from cgsccpInstMapNotFound object.

cgsccpGttErrorsUnequipedSS.name: cgsccpGttErrorsUnequipedSS
cgsccpGttErrorsUnequipedSS.description: This counter is incremented every time a global title translation could not be performed due to an unequipped subsystem (SS). This counter is derived from cgsccpInstQ752T7E7 object.

cgsccpGttErrorsSccpUnavailable.name: cgsccpGttErrorsSccpUnavailable
cgsccpGttErrorsSccpUnavailable.description: This counter is incremented every time a SCCP is unavailable at the GTT Mated Application. This counter is derived from cgsccpGttMapSccpUnavail object.

cgsccpGttErrorsDpcUnavailable.name: cgsccpGttErrorsDpcUnavailable
cgsccpGttErrorsDpcUnavailable.description: This counter is incremented every time a point code is unavailable at the GTT Mated Application. This counter is derived from cgsccpGttMapQ752T7E3Un object.

cgsccpGttErrorsSsUnavailable.name: cgsccpGttErrorsSsUnavailable
cgsccpGttErrorsSsUnavailable.description: This counter is incremented every time a subsystem is unavailable at the GTT Mated Application. This counter is derived from cgsccpGttMapQ752T7E5 object.

cgsccpGttErrorsDpcCongested.name: cgsccpGttErrorsDpcCongested
cgsccpGttErrorsDpcCongested.description: This counter is incremented every time a point code is congested at the GTT Mated Application. This counter is derived from cgsccpGttMapQ752T7E4 object.

cgsccpGttErrorsSsCongested.name: cgsccpGttErrorsSsCongested
cgsccpGttErrorsSsCongested.description: This counter is incremented every time a subsystem is congested at the GTT Mated Application. This counter is derived from cgsccpGttMapQ752T7E6 object.

cgsccpGttErrorsRouteFailure.name: cgsccpGttErrorsRouteFailure
cgsccpGttErrorsRouteFailure.description: This counter is incremented every time a the MTP3 layer failed at the GTT Mated Application. This counter is derived from cgsccpGttMapQ752T7E3Fail object.

cgsccpGttErrorsSccpUnqualified.name: cgsccpGttErrorsSccpUnqualified
cgsccpGttErrorsSccpUnqualified.description: This counter is incremented every time a global title translation is unsuccessful and the error type not covered by other specific error types. This counter is derived from cgsccpInstQ752Unqualified object.

cgsccpGttErrorsReassUnsupported.name: cgsccpGttErrorsReassUnsupported
cgsccpGttErrorsReassUnsupported.description: This counter is incremented every time when the incoming SCCP message needs to be dropped due to the unsupported reassembly feature. This counter is derived from cgsccpInstReassUnsup object.

cgsccpGttErrorsReassFailure.name: cgsccpGttErrorsReassFailure
cgsccpGttErrorsReassFailure.description: This counter is incremented every time when the incoming SCCP message needs to be dropped due to the reassembly failure. This counter is derived from cgsccpInstReassFail object.

cgsccpGttErrorsSegUnsupported.name: cgsccpGttErrorsSegUnsupported
cgsccpGttErrorsSegUnsupported.description: This counter is incremented every time when either SCCP message from a remote node or local SCCP stack needs to be dropped due to the unsupported segmentation feature. This counter is derived from cgsccpInstSegUnsup object.

cgsccpGttErrorsSegFailure.name: cgsccpGttErrorsSegFailure
cgsccpGttErrorsSegFailure.description: This counter is incremented every time when either SCCP message from a remote node or local SCCP stack needs to be dropped due to the segmentation failure. This counter is derived from cgsccpInstSegFail object.

cgsccpSSNTable.name: cgsccpSSNTable
cgsccpSSNTable.description: The SSN table provides a breakdown of SCCP measurements at local subsystem level.

cgsccpSSNEntry.name: cgsccpSSNEntry
cgsccpSSNEntry.description: Each table entry represents a specific local subsystem number(SSN).

cgsccpSSNNumProhibits.name: cgsccpSSNNumProhibits
cgsccpSSNNumProhibits.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 8.
cgsccpSSNNumProhibits.description: This counter is incremented every time this local subsystem transitions to prohibit state at this instance (Q752/8.9).

cgsccpSSNNumAllows.name: cgsccpSSNNumAllows
cgsccpSSNNumAllows.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 8.
cgsccpSSNNumAllows.description: This counter is incremented every time this local subsystem transitions to allowed state at this instance (Q752/8.10).

cgsccpSSNClassTable.name: cgsccpSSNClassTable
cgsccpSSNClassTable.description: The SSN Class table contains information about the number of UDT, XUDT, LUDT messages originated and terminated for a specific SSN and class. This provides the granularity of information required by Q752 elements 9.6 and 9.7

cgsccpSSNClassEntry.name: cgsccpSSNClassEntry
cgsccpSSNClassEntry.description: Each table entry represents a specific class and subsystem number(SSN).

cgsccpSSNClassUDTMsgsSent.name: cgsccpSSNClassUDTMsgsSent
cgsccpSSNClassUDTMsgsSent.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cgsccpSSNClassUDTMsgsSent.description: This counter is incremented every time a unitdata (UDT) message is sent for this SCCP class and SSN(Q752/9.6).

cgsccpSSNClassUDTMsgsRcvd.name: cgsccpSSNClassUDTMsgsRcvd
cgsccpSSNClassUDTMsgsRcvd.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cgsccpSSNClassUDTMsgsRcvd.description: This counter is incremented every time a unitdata (UDT) message is received for this SCCP class and SSN(Q752/9.7).

cgsccpSSNClassXUDTMsgsSent.name: cgsccpSSNClassXUDTMsgsSent
cgsccpSSNClassXUDTMsgsSent.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cgsccpSSNClassXUDTMsgsSent.description: This counter is incremented every time an extended unitdata (XUDT) message is sent for this SCCP class and SSN (Q752/9.6).

cgsccpSSNClassXUDTMsgsRcvd.name: cgsccpSSNClassXUDTMsgsRcvd
cgsccpSSNClassXUDTMsgsRcvd.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cgsccpSSNClassXUDTMsgsRcvd.description: This counter is incremented every time an extended unitdata (XUDT) message is received for this SCCP class and SSN (Q752/9.7).

cgsccpSSNClassLUDTMsgsSent.name: cgsccpSSNClassLUDTMsgsSent
cgsccpSSNClassLUDTMsgsSent.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cgsccpSSNClassLUDTMsgsSent.description: This counter is incremented every time a long unitdata (LUDT) message is sent for this SCCP class and SSN (Q752/9.6).

cgsccpSSNClassLUDTMsgsRcvd.name: cgsccpSSNClassLUDTMsgsRcvd
cgsccpSSNClassLUDTMsgsRcvd.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cgsccpSSNClassLUDTMsgsRcvd.description: This counter is incremented every time a long unitdata (LUDT) message is received for this SCCP class and SSN (Q752/9.7).

ciscoGsccpGttMapStateChange.name: ciscoGsccpGttMapStateChange
ciscoGsccpGttMapStateChange.description: The notification generated when a mated application subsystem changes to a new state. The value of cgsccpGttMapSsStatus indicates the new state for the subsystem.

ciscoGsccpGttLoadTable.name: ciscoGsccpGttLoadTable
ciscoGsccpGttLoadTable.description: This notification is generated whenever a load operation is started or completes.

ciscoGsccpGttErrors.name: ciscoGsccpGttErrors
ciscoGsccpGttErrors.description: This notification is generated whenever any global title error is encountered in last interval specified by the cgsccpGttErrorPeriod and the cgsccpInstErrorIndicator will be set to true. The notification will also be generated when errors have abated. The notification is generated after the number of recovery intervals as specified by the cgsccpGttErrorRecoveryCount object has passed without any global title errors.

ciscoGsccpSegReassUnsup.name: ciscoGsccpSegReassUnsup
ciscoGsccpSegReassUnsup.description: This notification is generated initially when a SCCP message is dropped due to a segmentation or reassembly unsupported or failure errors in last interval specified by the cgsccpGttErrorPeriod and the cgsccpInstErrorIndicator will be set to true. The notification will also be generated after the number of recovery intervals as specified by the cgsccpGttErrorRecoveryCount object has passed without any segmentation or reassembly unsupported errors.

ciscoGsccpSOGReceived.name: ciscoGsccpSOGReceived
ciscoGsccpSOGReceived.description: This notification is generated initially when a Subsystem Out-of-Service Grant is sent in response to a Subsystem Out-of-Service Request message. The affected PC and affected SSN are provided with this notification.

ciscoGsccpRmtCongestion.name: ciscoGsccpRmtCongestion
ciscoGsccpRmtCongestion.description: This notification is generated initially when congestion is experienced in the remote SCCP component for the first time in last interval specified by the cgsccpGttErrorPeriod. The notification is generated after the number of recovery intervals as specified by the cgsccpGttErrorRecoveryCount object has passed without any congestion errors and total number of local congestion observed for different congestion levels at the end of the interval along with the latest known congestion status for that remote signalling point will be provided.

ciscoGsccpLocalSsStateChange.name: ciscoGsccpLocalSsStateChange
ciscoGsccpLocalSsStateChange.description: The notification generated when a local application subsystem changes to a new state. The subsystem number and the latest subsystem state will be provided in this notification.
